<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-03T10:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-03T10:44:00-05:00" n="391" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.124a/97: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Carter</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-03T15:00:00-00:44">June 3, 1930—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 3—2:15 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>74. Dr. Smith informed that a clear case of yellow fever has been
                            reported next to Legation premises. This is first case of the year and
                            while under no apprehensions personally am reporting the case to the
                            diplomatic and consular body in Monrovia.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Carter</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>